text: It is amazing how far this technology has evolved.  Keep in mind, the mass of the robot is several feet higher than its feet and it is a bipod, two legs. Consider the amount of gyroscope controls it would require just to keep the thing vertically erect let alone semi-autonomous movements that would shift its center of gravity.  Personally, I find this drive toward robots very unsettling, unnerving and disturbing.  I am not in favor or robots at all except in repetitive manufacturing tasks.
